WEBVTT

00:02.540 --> 00:03.540
Kevin: My life
was going pretty terrible.

00:03.540 --> 00:04.960
I lost my job,

00:04.960 --> 00:06.580
had to move in with my sister
and my niece.

00:06.580 --> 00:09.580
And then, things got weird.

00:09.580 --> 00:12.420
Do not be afraid.

00:12.420 --> 00:14.330
Super weird.

00:14.330 --> 00:17.330
Yvette: In every generation,
there are 36 righteous souls.

00:17.330 --> 00:20.080
You are the last
of the righteous.

00:20.080 --> 00:21.420
Who are you talking to?

00:21.420 --> 00:23.040
She can't see me.

00:23.040 --> 00:25.830
She's done a pretty good job
convincing me she's real.

00:27.460 --> 00:30.580
And now I have to do something
I haven't had to do before --

00:30.580 --> 00:34.170
put others before myself,
help people.

00:34.170 --> 00:35.750
What just happened?
That guy...

00:35.750 --> 00:38.040
was wearing
so much Drakkar Noir.
[ Scoffs ]

00:38.040 --> 00:40.500
I am the last guy you'd
ever want to save the world,

00:40.500 --> 00:42.830
but I think
I can figure it out...

00:42.830 --> 00:43.750
probably.

00:45.710 --> 00:47.920
[ Crickets chirping ]

00:51.420 --> 00:53.960
[ "Once Upon a Dream" plays ]

01:00.580 --> 01:03.540
♪ I know you ♪

01:03.540 --> 01:08.790
♪ I walked with you
once upon a dream ♪

01:08.790 --> 01:11.580
♪ I know you ♪

01:11.580 --> 01:17.040
♪ The gleam in your eyes
is so familiar a gleam ♪

01:17.040 --> 01:18.620
♪ Yet I know it's true ♪

01:18.620 --> 01:20.170
[ Mumbling ]
I eat all the pies.

01:21.790 --> 01:23.380
I know you do.

01:25.500 --> 01:28.540
♪ But if I know you ♪

01:28.540 --> 01:30.830
♪ I know what you'll do ♪

01:30.830 --> 01:34.500
♪ You'll love me at once ♪

01:34.500 --> 01:36.500
♪ The way you did ♪

01:36.500 --> 01:42.500
[ Grunting ]
♪ Once upon a dream ♪

01:42.500 --> 01:44.880
♪ La, la, la, la ♪

01:44.880 --> 01:47.170
♪ La, ah, ah ♪

01:47.170 --> 01:50.210
♪ Ah, ah, ah ♪

01:50.210 --> 01:53.120
♪ But if I know you ♪

01:53.120 --> 01:56.120
♪ I know what you'll do ♪

01:56.120 --> 01:59.290
♪ You'll love me at once ♪

01:59.290 --> 02:01.120
♪ The way you did ♪
Marco!

02:01.120 --> 02:07.120
♪ Once upon a dream ♪

02:07.120 --> 02:13.580
♪♪

02:13.580 --> 02:15.120
[ Splat ]

02:15.120 --> 02:18.620
♪♪

02:18.620 --> 02:20.710
Razzmatazz.

02:20.710 --> 02:26.500
♪♪

02:26.500 --> 02:33.170
♪ And I know it's true ♪
[ Giggles ]

02:33.170 --> 02:39.000
♪ That visions
are seldom all they seem ♪

02:39.000 --> 02:42.080
[ Owl hoots ]
♪ But if I know you ♪

02:42.080 --> 02:45.710
♪ I know what you'll do ♪

02:45.710 --> 02:48.710
♪ You'll love me at once ♪

02:48.710 --> 02:50.710
♪ The way you did ♪
[ Groans ]

02:50.710 --> 02:53.210
Morning.
You sleep well?

02:53.210 --> 02:56.000
Mm-hmm.
Oh, I had the best dream.

02:56.000 --> 02:59.080
I was...floating around
with a...

03:00.380 --> 03:01.750
...balloon.

03:01.750 --> 03:02.960
I wouldn't do that.

03:05.580 --> 03:08.040
[ Gasps ]

03:09.330 --> 03:10.500
Man: Don't do it!

03:10.500 --> 03:12.170
W-W-What the hell?
Woman: No, man! Please!

03:12.170 --> 03:13.330
You don't
have to do this!

03:13.330 --> 03:15.920
Come down!
Let's talk about it.

03:15.920 --> 03:17.460
[ Clears throat ]

03:17.460 --> 03:18.790
So, question.

03:18.790 --> 03:20.040
Go ahead.

03:20.040 --> 03:21.040
Am I still asleep?

03:21.040 --> 03:22.830
No.
No, you are not.

03:22.830 --> 03:24.670
Ooh. Okay.

03:24.670 --> 03:25.670
Breathe.

03:25.670 --> 03:27.000
Kevin?!

03:30.960 --> 03:32.000
Ohhh.

03:32.000 --> 03:34.210
Hi!

03:38.500 --> 03:41.330
We'll take Mr. Finn
from here.
Take him where, exactly?

03:41.330 --> 03:43.750
Amy: Back home.

03:43.750 --> 03:46.040
Thank you for your discretion,
Mandy.

03:46.040 --> 03:47.920
I'll make sure
he gets there safely.

03:47.920 --> 03:51.080
He's clearly unstable.
You want to just let him go?

03:51.080 --> 03:52.290
He says
he was sleepwalking.

03:52.290 --> 03:54.040
Up six flights of stairs?

03:54.040 --> 03:55.670
Hey, I've done push-ups
in my sleep.

03:55.670 --> 03:56.880
[ Scoffs ]

03:56.880 --> 03:58.920
Come on, Mandy.
The freaks come out at night.

03:58.920 --> 04:00.460
You called the police
to handle this.

04:00.460 --> 04:02.210
This is me handling it.
[ Air hissing ]

04:02.210 --> 04:04.460
Mr. Finn's never done
anything like this before.

04:04.460 --> 04:06.830
Dr. Cabrera is
a respected faculty member.

04:06.830 --> 04:08.670
She'd never do anything
to bring trouble to this school.

04:08.670 --> 04:09.790
Neither would her brother.
Right?

04:09.790 --> 04:11.710
Not intentionally, no.

04:11.710 --> 04:12.750
[ Chuckles nervously ]

04:12.750 --> 04:15.000
You know what?

04:15.000 --> 04:16.080
He's your problem.

04:21.210 --> 04:23.710
I promise you this isn't
what it looks like, okay?

04:23.710 --> 04:24.750
[ Scoffs ]

04:24.750 --> 04:27.000
I was sleepwalking,

04:27.000 --> 04:29.040
but I am sorry
that it happened at your work.

04:29.040 --> 04:31.250
I don't care about that.

04:31.250 --> 04:33.500
Kevin, when was the last time
you talked to Dr. Sloane?

04:33.500 --> 04:35.380
I know he's left you
a few messages.

04:35.380 --> 04:37.000
[ Clears throat ]
I'll call him.

04:37.000 --> 04:39.710
I'll call him to...day.

04:39.710 --> 04:42.790
Yeah, well, I want you to talk
to someone here in town, okay?

04:42.790 --> 04:44.750
Dr. Elizabeth Salentine. She's
a counselor here on campus.

04:44.750 --> 04:46.830
She's a friend of mine,
and I bet you

04:46.830 --> 04:48.920
that she will even be able
to squeeze you in later today.

04:48.920 --> 04:51.540
Well, uh, today --
yeah, I'm, uh, I'm busy.

04:51.540 --> 04:53.670
I'm very busy.
Plus, I don't really --

04:53.670 --> 04:57.500
Kevin, this is -- this is
really important to me, okay?

04:57.500 --> 04:59.290
I'm scared.

04:59.290 --> 05:01.880
Okay, okay.
All right, I'll go.

05:01.880 --> 05:03.330
For a price.

05:04.500 --> 05:07.210
Can you find and purchase
some pants for me?

05:08.960 --> 05:10.330
Well?
I was asleep.

05:10.330 --> 05:11.420
God.

05:12.790 --> 05:14.460
So, just to clarify,

05:14.460 --> 05:17.960
you watched me walk across town
in my underwear,

05:17.960 --> 05:19.620
and you didn't wake me up?

05:19.620 --> 05:21.040
Didn't even occur to you?

05:21.040 --> 05:22.960
You can't just wake
a sleepwalker.

05:22.960 --> 05:24.880
Their heart could pop
like a tick.

05:24.880 --> 05:27.330
-Really?
-No.

05:27.330 --> 05:29.420
You're not great,
you know that?

05:29.420 --> 05:31.460
We had to see
where the balloon led you.

05:31.460 --> 05:33.750
Well, ta-da!
It led to therapy.

05:33.750 --> 05:35.830
Good!
[ Scoffs ]

05:35.830 --> 05:38.580
Therapy is a healthy thing.
We all need someone to talk to.

05:38.580 --> 05:40.960
[ Air hisses ]

05:40.960 --> 05:43.170
Is --
Is that your pants?

05:43.170 --> 05:50.830
♪♪

05:50.830 --> 05:52.500
I'd leave that
out of the session.

05:52.500 --> 05:59.420
♪♪

06:01.040 --> 06:03.290
[ Clears throat ]

06:03.290 --> 06:05.880
Excuse me.
I am looking for...

06:05.880 --> 06:08.290
Pookie?

06:08.290 --> 06:10.380
I-I-I mean, I'm Pookie.

06:10.380 --> 06:11.960
I mean, I'm Deb.
And Pookie.

06:11.960 --> 06:13.000
Where did you find that?

06:13.000 --> 06:14.710
That's mine.

06:14.710 --> 06:17.750
Um, it...
kind of found me.

06:17.750 --> 06:19.290
Uh, it must've known
I was gonna see you.

06:19.290 --> 06:20.420
[ Both chuckle ]

06:20.420 --> 06:21.920
Uh, I'm Kevin.

06:21.920 --> 06:23.170
Well, thank you, Kevin.
[ Chuckles ]

06:26.290 --> 06:27.710
Oh.
Can I help you?

06:27.710 --> 06:29.830
Yes. Um...

06:29.830 --> 06:30.830
Oh!

06:30.830 --> 06:32.620
Congratulations.

06:32.620 --> 06:34.380
When's the big day?

06:34.380 --> 06:36.710
Uh, well, we actually
had a quickie wedding
a couple years ago,

06:36.710 --> 06:38.710
but now we're making it real.
-Mm.

06:38.710 --> 06:40.620
Kind of like
a Vegas thing?

06:40.620 --> 06:42.210
No, actually --
a cancer thing.

06:44.000 --> 06:45.210
I'm so sorry.

06:45.210 --> 06:47.290
-I'm in remission.
-Oh.

06:47.290 --> 06:48.620
And now
Ben wants a big wedding

06:48.620 --> 06:50.290
cause, you know,
bride's not gonna die.

06:50.290 --> 06:54.460
[ Laughing ]

06:54.460 --> 06:56.880
Now I'm laughing about cancer,
and that feels weird.

06:56.880 --> 06:59.000
-Uh, lock it down, Kevin.
-Okay. Okay.

06:59.000 --> 07:02.540
I seriously can't deal
with wedding planning.

07:02.540 --> 07:04.330
I mean, DJ or band?

07:04.330 --> 07:06.960
Cotton
or linen tablecloths?

07:06.960 --> 07:09.960
Uh...wine or liquor?
Who cares?

07:09.960 --> 07:14.120
Jazz band, Pima cotton,
signature cocktail.

07:14.120 --> 07:17.830
Jazz band, Pima cotton,
signature cocktails?

07:20.460 --> 07:22.540
Yeah.

07:22.540 --> 07:24.880
Actually, yeah,
that sounds perfect.

07:26.040 --> 07:27.620
You're really good at this.

07:27.620 --> 07:29.210
-Oh, thank you.
-Thank you.

07:32.170 --> 07:33.880
It was really nice
meeting you.

07:33.880 --> 07:35.080
You too.
[ Chuckles ]

07:35.080 --> 07:37.040
But now I have to go
to the florist

07:37.040 --> 07:39.830
and pretend like
I have an opinion about azaleas.

07:39.830 --> 07:43.420
Uh, w-- uh, well,
I know a lot about flowers, too.

07:43.420 --> 07:45.960
Do I know about flowers?

07:45.960 --> 07:47.580
I do.

07:47.580 --> 07:50.500
I know a ton about flowers,
so I'm happy to help.

07:50.500 --> 07:51.880
Aren't you here
for an appointment?

07:54.420 --> 07:55.620
No.

07:55.620 --> 07:57.880
No, I --
I was just here, uh,

07:57.880 --> 08:01.670
looking for literature
on...

08:01.670 --> 08:03.290
chlamydia.

08:03.290 --> 08:04.620
It's for a friend.

08:04.620 --> 08:06.040
Okay.

08:06.040 --> 08:10.120
♪♪

08:10.120 --> 08:11.580
So, I don't want you
to be worried,

08:11.580 --> 08:13.380
but sleepwalking
is a pretty common thing.

08:13.380 --> 08:14.380
I Googled it.

08:14.380 --> 08:16.460
People sleepwalk
across town?

08:16.460 --> 08:18.670
Well, that was probably
a little less common,

08:18.670 --> 08:21.580
but the good news is
is I got him to go to therapy.

08:21.580 --> 08:23.000
He's actually at an appointment
right now.

08:23.000 --> 08:24.880
No, he's not.

08:24.880 --> 08:27.120
Are you kidding me?

08:30.540 --> 08:31.540
-Hey, babe.
-Hey!

08:31.540 --> 08:32.880
Sorry I'm late.

08:32.880 --> 08:35.670
Hey, what do you think about
a cascading-dahlia display?

08:35.670 --> 08:39.080
It's probably close to $10,000,
but hear me out.
Ooh!

08:39.080 --> 08:40.790
I-I want
something simple.

08:40.790 --> 08:43.210
-Okay.
-Sorry. Who are you?

08:43.210 --> 08:45.500
Ooh, Ben,
this is Kevin.

08:45.500 --> 08:46.790
He's a little weird,

08:46.790 --> 08:48.710
but I kid you not,
he's the damn Wedding Whisperer.

08:49.620 --> 08:51.250
Is that so?

08:51.250 --> 08:53.420
-Peonies.
-Peonies?

08:53.420 --> 08:55.920
Elaborate.

08:55.920 --> 08:58.080
Peonies will buy you
all the "wow" factor...
Peonies will buy you

08:58.080 --> 09:00.750
...that you're looking for.
...all the "wow" factor
that you're looking for.

09:00.750 --> 09:03.880
While being a sturdy flower
that will look flawless...
While being a sturdy flower
that will look flawless...

09:03.880 --> 09:07.120
...from walking down to
the aisle to the bouquet toss.
...from walking down to
the aisle to the bouquet toss.

09:07.120 --> 09:08.380
[ Chuckles ]

09:08.380 --> 09:10.250
[ Chuckles ]

09:10.250 --> 09:12.330
-He's good.
-Right?

09:12.330 --> 09:13.920
Amy:
Who are those people?

09:13.920 --> 09:16.960
Maybe it's flower therapy?

09:16.960 --> 09:18.330
That's not a thing.

09:18.330 --> 09:23.040
♪♪

09:23.040 --> 09:24.960
[ Engine starts ]
Where are we going?

09:24.960 --> 09:27.120
Home -- to get your uncle
the help that he needs.

09:30.290 --> 09:31.380
[ Sniffs ]

09:31.380 --> 09:34.500
-Hmm?
-I mean, I like it,

09:34.500 --> 09:36.170
but Deb will say
it looks like cilantro.

09:37.540 --> 09:38.710
Cilantro makes her
want to kill everyone.

09:38.710 --> 09:40.790
[ Laughs ]

09:40.790 --> 09:43.460
You guys know each other
really well.

09:43.460 --> 09:47.210
Yeah, we grew up together --
six doors down.

09:47.210 --> 09:48.120
We were best friends.

09:49.580 --> 09:50.830
Took cancer
for me to admit

09:50.830 --> 09:52.710
that I'd been in love with her
my whole life.

09:54.250 --> 09:56.290
I don't know
how I got so lucky.

09:56.290 --> 09:59.710
Oh, yeah.
What about these?

09:59.710 --> 10:00.960
Oh.

10:00.960 --> 10:03.080
Deb, carnations?
Are you serious?

10:03.080 --> 10:05.830
[ Indistinct conversation ]

10:05.830 --> 10:11.830
♪♪

10:11.830 --> 10:17.880
♪♪

10:17.880 --> 10:19.830
Hey, Yvette!

10:19.830 --> 10:22.960
A-Ava?
What are you doing here?

10:22.960 --> 10:25.120
Just thought I'd check in
on my bud!

10:25.120 --> 10:27.380
Thought
maybe we could hang.

10:27.380 --> 10:29.670
Hang? Uh, I'm --
I'm kind of busy right now.

10:29.670 --> 10:31.750
Of course.

10:31.750 --> 10:33.920
Must be nice.

10:33.920 --> 10:36.290
That your guy?

10:36.290 --> 10:39.040
Yep. That's Kevin.

10:39.040 --> 10:42.420
The shredded, hot guy?
Uh, he looks righteous.

10:42.420 --> 10:44.880
I can see why you'd want
to keep him to yourself.

10:44.880 --> 10:47.120
Mm...no, the other one.

10:48.500 --> 10:50.210
Oh.

10:50.210 --> 10:52.000
Yeah!
[ Chuckles ]

10:52.000 --> 10:54.000
Yeah,
I'm sure he'll pan out.

10:56.040 --> 10:58.330
So, how are things?

10:58.330 --> 11:00.420
How -- How are things?

11:00.420 --> 11:01.960
Um, not good.

11:01.960 --> 11:04.120
We're trying to save the world,
and all I've got is...

11:04.120 --> 11:07.120
well, not that guy.

11:07.120 --> 11:08.460
Don't complain.

11:08.460 --> 11:11.330
At least you have
a soul to protect.

11:11.330 --> 11:13.540
You...

11:13.540 --> 11:15.960
You know your mission here
isn't over, right?

11:15.960 --> 11:17.710
You and the others
still need to find out

11:17.710 --> 11:20.120
what happened
to the other 35 righteous.

11:20.120 --> 11:21.790
Yeah.
I guess you're right.

11:21.790 --> 11:25.120
I -- I am right.

11:25.120 --> 11:29.250
There's something or someone
working against us out there.

11:29.250 --> 11:31.880
36 souls don't just disappear
like that.

11:31.880 --> 11:33.960
You mean 35.

11:33.960 --> 11:36.120
See, you found yours
in time.

11:36.120 --> 11:38.710
Maybe we should
get everyone together --

11:38.710 --> 11:39.830
talk strategy.

11:39.830 --> 11:42.080
I'll round up the troops.

11:42.080 --> 11:48.750
♪♪

11:48.750 --> 11:50.120
Ahh, I needed this.

11:50.120 --> 11:52.380
Planning a wedding
for two good people?

11:52.380 --> 11:54.040
This is the reason
I signed up for this job.

11:54.040 --> 11:55.380
You didn't sign up.

11:58.920 --> 12:00.000
Amy: Hey.

12:00.000 --> 12:02.380
Uh, look who's here.

12:02.380 --> 12:04.250
Hiya, Kevin.

12:04.250 --> 12:05.580
Dr. Sloane.

12:07.710 --> 12:09.330
Who is this?
What's happening?

12:09.330 --> 12:11.170
My...therapist.
[ Chuckles nervously ]

12:11.170 --> 12:12.670
My therapist
from New York,

12:12.670 --> 12:15.460
who is suddenly here,
who I didn't expect.

12:15.460 --> 12:17.380
Hello, Dr. Sloane.

12:17.380 --> 12:18.620
Stop talking weird.

12:18.620 --> 12:21.210
Now I will stop...
talking weird.

12:21.210 --> 12:23.120
[ Clears throat ]

12:23.120 --> 12:26.210
I was in Houston at a conference
when I got the call.

12:27.790 --> 12:30.120
Um...I'm sorry.

12:30.120 --> 12:31.580
What --
What call, now?

12:31.580 --> 12:32.790
From me.

12:32.790 --> 12:34.500
I called him.

12:34.500 --> 12:37.580
You wouldn't take the help
that was offered, so I'm...

12:37.580 --> 12:39.540
bringing the help to you.

12:39.540 --> 12:43.920
♪♪

12:49.170 --> 12:52.500
It's just that ambush therapy
generally isn't productive.

12:52.500 --> 12:54.330
Well, neither is skipping
the therapy session

12:54.330 --> 12:55.710
that I set up for you.

12:55.710 --> 12:57.000
I was busy.

12:57.000 --> 12:58.000
You were at a flower shop.

12:58.000 --> 12:59.620
Are you following me?

12:59.620 --> 13:01.330
-Calm down, Kevin.
-I'm calm!

13:01.330 --> 13:03.960
Okay, everyone's having
strong emotions.

13:03.960 --> 13:05.250
Let's step back.

13:05.250 --> 13:07.040
My emotions are fine.

13:07.040 --> 13:08.540
Your emotions led you

13:08.540 --> 13:11.380
to invading
your brother's privacy, Amy.

13:11.380 --> 13:13.040
Your intentions
might've been good,

13:13.040 --> 13:14.790
but it's still
a violation.

13:14.790 --> 13:16.540
Thank you, Dr. Sloane.

13:16.540 --> 13:20.670
And your behavior has reportedly
ranged from odd to alarming.

13:20.670 --> 13:23.830
Standing on
the edge of buildings?

13:23.830 --> 13:25.830
Sleepwalking --
sleepwalking...

13:25.830 --> 13:27.460
onto the edge of buildings.

13:27.460 --> 13:29.960
Which in and of itself
could indicate a problem --

13:29.960 --> 13:33.670
anxiety,
a reaction to meds, PTSD.

13:33.670 --> 13:36.000
But it wasn't
any of those things.

13:36.000 --> 13:38.670
Kevin, you've been
avoiding my calls,

13:38.670 --> 13:40.830
which is certainly
within your rights,

13:40.830 --> 13:42.080
but please acknowledge

13:42.080 --> 13:44.380
you're neglecting
your emotional health.

13:44.380 --> 13:47.040
I'm -- I'm not neglecting
my emotional health.

13:47.040 --> 13:49.500
I've just been very busy,
and...

13:49.500 --> 13:52.120
Uh, ye-- actually,
I-I've got to go.

13:52.120 --> 13:54.880
W-Where?
Where do you have to go?

13:54.880 --> 13:57.250
To help some friends out
with their signature cocktails.

13:57.250 --> 13:58.380
What friends?

13:58.380 --> 14:01.000
New friends, Amy!
People make new friends.

14:01.000 --> 14:02.920
Okay, but you --
Why are you helping them?

14:02.920 --> 14:04.620
Kevin, you can't answer that.
Walk away.

14:04.620 --> 14:07.000
Because I tasted
your birth control pills

14:07.000 --> 14:08.880
when we were 15!

14:08.880 --> 14:10.790
Do you se-- This is exactly
what I'm talking about!

14:10.790 --> 14:12.330
God!
Kevin,
what is going on?

14:12.330 --> 14:14.670
Bail. Get out.
Leave!

14:14.670 --> 14:17.170
Dr. Sloane.
Always a pleasure.

14:17.170 --> 14:19.040
Amy, you're
a nightmare person.

14:19.040 --> 14:24.250
♪♪

14:24.250 --> 14:26.290
Can you please explain to me
why I can't tell anyone

14:26.290 --> 14:28.330
who I am, who you are,
or what I'm doing?

14:28.330 --> 14:29.330
You just can't.

14:29.330 --> 14:30.670
I only told you

14:30.670 --> 14:32.960
because desperate times
call for desperate measures.

14:32.960 --> 14:34.500
The less you know,
the better.

14:34.500 --> 14:35.710
Well, what do I do?

14:35.710 --> 14:37.750
I can't keep blurting out
stupid stuff to her.

14:37.750 --> 14:39.170
Lie.

14:39.170 --> 14:39.960
What?

14:39.960 --> 14:41.540
Lie -- to bend the truth

14:41.540 --> 14:44.170
on a scale of "little white"
to "bald-faced."

14:44.170 --> 14:46.420
Please, I worked on Wall Street.
I know what a lie is.

14:46.420 --> 14:47.920
I'm just surprised

14:47.920 --> 14:49.750
that's something
an angel would suggest.

14:49.750 --> 14:50.830
I'm not an angel.

14:50.830 --> 14:52.420
I believe in what's right,

14:52.420 --> 14:54.040
and if a lie is told
for a just cause,

14:54.040 --> 14:55.670
then it's justified.

14:55.670 --> 14:59.120
You are on a mission to bring
balance to the universe.

14:59.120 --> 15:01.250
If that isn't a good cause,
I don't know what it is.

15:01.250 --> 15:03.830
-I can't lie to Amy!
-[ Sighs ]

15:03.830 --> 15:06.750
That woman has known me
every second of my life.
She can always tell.

15:06.750 --> 15:09.750
Lying is a performance,
like acting,

15:09.750 --> 15:12.420
a craft that typically takes
years of study to perfect,

15:12.420 --> 15:14.580
but we don't have time
for that nonsense,

15:14.580 --> 15:16.670
so crash course.

15:16.670 --> 15:20.380
Now, a good performer
needs proper motivation,

15:20.380 --> 15:22.420
and I'm gonna give you
that motivation.

15:22.420 --> 15:24.960
[ Thunder rumbles ]

15:24.960 --> 15:27.830
[ Dog barks in distance ]

15:27.830 --> 15:30.960
I'm gonna ask you a question,
and I want you to lie,

15:30.960 --> 15:32.290
and I better believe it.

15:32.290 --> 15:34.330
And what --
what if you don't believe it?

15:34.330 --> 15:36.000
You'll be struck
by lightning.

15:36.000 --> 15:37.540
[ Laughs ]

15:37.540 --> 15:39.790
Okay. I get it.

15:39.790 --> 15:41.920
You're lying to teach me.
Good one.

15:41.920 --> 15:43.750
[ Thunder crashes ]

15:43.750 --> 15:47.500
Why are you helping Deb and Ben
plan their wedding?

15:47.500 --> 15:50.000
I mean...

15:50.000 --> 15:52.880
I've always wanted to be
a wedding planner.

15:52.880 --> 15:54.830
[ Thunder crashes ]
And...y-y--

15:54.830 --> 15:56.380
[ Chuckles nervously ]

15:56.380 --> 15:59.120
Mnh-mnh. You're not gonna --
you're not gonna do this,

15:59.120 --> 16:00.830
because it's your job
to protect me.

16:00.830 --> 16:03.460
Lots of people get struck
by lightning and survive.

16:03.460 --> 16:05.790
Why are you helping
with their wedding, Kevin?

16:05.790 --> 16:10.620
Because -- Because I'm --
I've -- I've...

16:10.620 --> 16:12.830
I've always thought
of being a wedding planner.

16:12.830 --> 16:14.040
[ Thunder crashes ]
Ohhhh!

16:14.040 --> 16:15.580
Mnh!

16:15.580 --> 16:17.670
I love weddings.
I want to be a wedding planner.

16:17.670 --> 16:19.210
I have seen every episode
of "Say Yes to the Dress"!

16:21.290 --> 16:22.580
Passable.

16:22.580 --> 16:24.290
Thank you.

16:24.290 --> 16:25.750
And also, you're insane.

16:25.750 --> 16:27.250
I like your strategy

16:27.250 --> 16:29.670
of adding a kernel of truth
to help sell it.

16:29.670 --> 16:32.000
What is
"Say Yes to the Dress"?
Ohh!

16:32.000 --> 16:33.830
It's an awesome
television program

16:33.830 --> 16:35.960
that I enjoy
while I'm folding laundry.

16:35.960 --> 16:37.880
It's kind of like
a documentary.

16:37.880 --> 16:40.170
Kind of exactly
like a documentary.

16:40.170 --> 16:42.080
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

16:44.880 --> 16:47.250
Is Ben coming?

16:47.250 --> 16:48.790
Deb?

16:48.790 --> 16:50.290
Um, where's Ben?

16:50.290 --> 16:51.580
Oh,
he's on call tonight.

16:51.580 --> 16:52.750
Well,
he is missing out

16:52.750 --> 16:55.710
on some delicious
signature cocktails.

16:55.710 --> 16:59.330
First up, we have the
Elderflower White Cosmopolitan,

16:59.330 --> 17:02.250
AKA
"The Happily Elder After."

17:02.250 --> 17:05.420
Uh, so,
this particular liqueur --

17:05.420 --> 17:07.000
Uh, Deb. Whoa, Deb!

17:07.000 --> 17:08.790
Sampling, remember?
We're just...

17:08.790 --> 17:10.080
Mmm.
...sampling.

17:10.080 --> 17:11.920
Uh...
What's in this one?

17:11.920 --> 17:13.250
-"The BFF"...
-Ah.

17:13.250 --> 17:15.920
...because you and Ben
are best friends forever.

17:15.920 --> 17:19.250
-Got it.
-So, you'll notice the apricot.

17:19.250 --> 17:20.920
Mm-hmm.
But there's a little hint
of jasmine...

17:20.920 --> 17:23.330
Mm.
...and, uh, and whiskey.

17:23.330 --> 17:24.830
There is a lot of whiskey
in there...

17:24.830 --> 17:26.330
Deb.

17:26.330 --> 17:27.750
-Whew!
-You okay?

17:27.750 --> 17:29.710
-Top-shelf.
-[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

17:29.710 --> 17:30.540
Okay, which one's next?

17:30.540 --> 17:32.960
Um...

17:32.960 --> 17:34.880
Look.

17:34.880 --> 17:37.710
It's -- It --
It's just jitters, okay?

17:37.710 --> 17:41.670
Everyone gets cold feet,
even...

17:41.670 --> 17:43.290
people who are
already married.

17:44.750 --> 17:47.330
Look, if this big-wedding stuff
is too much,

17:47.330 --> 17:49.000
just say the word,
and we'll call it off

17:49.000 --> 17:50.290
and do something simple.

17:50.290 --> 17:53.620
What if we called off
the marriage?

17:53.620 --> 17:54.620
[ Chuckles ]

17:54.620 --> 17:56.120
What?

17:56.120 --> 17:58.080
Uh, nothing.
That was a joke.

17:58.080 --> 18:00.290
[ Chuckles ]
That was not a joke.

18:00.290 --> 18:04.330
You said it to the table.
No one tells jokes to tables.

18:04.330 --> 18:07.420
Um...

18:07.420 --> 18:09.210
Deb.

18:09.210 --> 18:10.420
Come on.

18:10.420 --> 18:12.460
I'm -- I'm...

18:12.460 --> 18:14.710
I'm your damn
Wedding Whisperer.

18:14.710 --> 18:17.380
You know,
you can tell me anything.

18:19.080 --> 18:21.210
I don't want to be married
anymore.

18:22.420 --> 18:24.080
Hmm.

18:24.080 --> 18:25.210
I was dying.

18:26.540 --> 18:29.500
And then this great guy
tells me he loves me,

18:29.500 --> 18:31.250
and he takes care of me,

18:31.250 --> 18:33.960
and I go with that,
and it was amazing.

18:33.960 --> 18:35.790
Mm-hmm.

18:35.790 --> 18:37.880
And then I got better.

18:37.880 --> 18:39.830
But that's a good thing.

18:39.830 --> 18:41.540
-I know!
-Okay.

18:41.540 --> 18:46.120
When we got married,
"forever" was 6 to 12 months.

18:47.580 --> 18:49.880
Now...

18:49.880 --> 18:52.170
it's my whole life.

18:52.170 --> 18:54.210
Mm.

18:54.210 --> 18:56.170
I don't know what to do.

18:56.170 --> 18:59.120
Uh...

19:03.330 --> 19:06.620
I think you need
to tell Ben how you feel.

19:06.620 --> 19:09.620
No, he's my best friend.
No, he deserves to be happy.

19:09.620 --> 19:11.880
Yeah, but don't you?

19:11.880 --> 19:13.880
[ Exhales ]

19:13.880 --> 19:15.880
I'm gonna throw up.

19:15.880 --> 19:16.920
And cry.

19:16.920 --> 19:17.790
Yep.
I'll be right back.

19:17.790 --> 19:19.540
O...kay.

19:19.540 --> 19:22.290
I'm supposed to break up
this marriage, aren't I?

19:22.290 --> 19:25.250
Yeah, that sounds like
the universe I know.

19:25.250 --> 19:26.670
I didn't sign up
for this.

19:26.670 --> 19:28.120
You didn't sign up.

19:30.380 --> 19:31.290
Too much ginger
in this one.

19:35.880 --> 19:37.080
So,
the hotel was okay?

19:37.080 --> 19:38.540
It was lovely.
Thanks.

19:38.540 --> 19:40.330
Good. Great.

19:40.330 --> 19:42.750
I'm sure Kevin will be down
any minute.

19:42.750 --> 19:44.750
He's not
much of an early bird.

19:44.750 --> 19:47.960
Let him rest.
It'll give us a minute to talk.

19:47.960 --> 19:50.080
[ Floorboards creak ]
Oh!

19:50.080 --> 19:51.250
There he is now.
[ Chuckles ]

19:52.500 --> 19:54.830
He's gone.
Left hours ago.

19:54.830 --> 19:57.500
-What?
-Guess he is an early bird.

19:57.500 --> 19:59.460
How you doing?
I'm Clark.

19:59.460 --> 20:01.080
Cool.

20:01.080 --> 20:02.210
Reese!

20:02.210 --> 20:05.540
Ah, to be young
and dismissive.

20:05.540 --> 20:06.670
I'm sorry. She's...

20:06.670 --> 20:09.670
A perfectly normal
teenager.

20:09.670 --> 20:12.580
You can relax, Amy.
I'm not here to shrink you.

20:12.580 --> 20:14.580
[ Chuckles ]

20:14.580 --> 20:16.580
Actually,
I don't think

20:16.580 --> 20:18.040
I'm gonna be shrinking
anyone here today.

20:19.790 --> 20:21.710
Look, I'm sorry.

20:21.710 --> 20:23.710
I shouldn't have tried
to force it.

20:23.710 --> 20:25.580
I overstepped.

20:25.580 --> 20:27.040
No.

20:27.040 --> 20:28.920
No, you're a good sister,
Amy.

20:30.500 --> 20:32.330
Kevin's lucky to have you.

20:32.330 --> 20:34.790
I don't know
if that's true.

20:34.790 --> 20:37.330
You shouldn't
blame yourself.

20:39.120 --> 20:40.540
I don't.
[ Door opens ]

20:40.540 --> 20:42.040
[ Scoffs ]

20:42.040 --> 20:43.420
Why would you say that?

20:45.420 --> 20:48.880
Because when a person
attempts suicide,

20:48.880 --> 20:51.120
it's common
for those closest to him

20:51.120 --> 20:53.420
to ask themselves,
"What did I miss?

20:53.420 --> 20:56.000
Was there something
I could've done?"

21:01.120 --> 21:03.120
You need to know, Amy,
that...

21:03.120 --> 21:07.000
Kevin is not
your responsibility.

21:07.000 --> 21:09.920
Everything isn't
your responsibility.

21:11.920 --> 21:13.500
You lost your husband

21:13.500 --> 21:16.210
to nothing more
than the whim of fate.

21:16.210 --> 21:18.710
It's okay
to be a little selfish.

21:18.710 --> 21:21.250
-Take care of yourself, Amy.
-Okay.

21:21.250 --> 21:23.460
Thanks, Dr. Sloane.
I'm sorry to waste your time.

21:23.460 --> 21:24.830
Have a good trip home.

21:27.000 --> 21:29.290
[ Sighs ]

21:29.290 --> 21:30.380
Reese?

21:30.380 --> 21:33.040
What?

21:33.040 --> 21:36.120
I am gonna go into town
and spy on Kevin.

21:36.120 --> 21:37.420
Want to come?

21:39.540 --> 21:41.620
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

21:41.620 --> 21:43.710
[ Sighs ]

21:43.710 --> 21:45.790
Working hard, K-Dog!

21:45.790 --> 21:47.210
[ Laughs ]

21:47.210 --> 21:49.170
-You need some brain food.
-Oh!

21:49.170 --> 21:51.380
-[ Sighs ]
-What's the project?

21:51.380 --> 21:54.880
Oh, it's a-a seating chart
for a wedding.

21:54.880 --> 21:57.670
Oh, my God!
That's amazing, man!

21:57.670 --> 21:59.080
Mazel!

21:59.080 --> 22:00.920
No, no!
Not my -- Not my wedding.

22:00.920 --> 22:02.880
It's, uh...

22:02.880 --> 22:05.580
actually, it's a wedding
that shouldn't even happen.

22:05.580 --> 22:07.750
I got to...

22:07.750 --> 22:09.580
I've got to
break this couple up.

22:09.580 --> 22:12.830
Might I suggest
a crippling gambling addiction?

22:13.960 --> 22:17.000
Online poker
ends relationships quick.

22:18.460 --> 22:20.420
Tyler, I worry about you.

22:20.420 --> 22:22.790
What are you talking about?
My life's awesome.

22:22.790 --> 22:24.040
Your life's garbage.

22:24.040 --> 22:25.580
Don't forget
to dump the grease traps.

22:25.580 --> 22:28.040
Thanks for the reminder,
Lucille!

22:29.620 --> 22:30.620
Ah, hey, Kristin!

22:30.620 --> 22:31.790
-Hey.
-Sit here.

22:31.790 --> 22:33.210
What are you guys up to?

22:33.210 --> 22:35.920
Breaking up a wedding.
Want to help?

22:35.920 --> 22:38.040
-Uh...
-It's complicated.

22:38.040 --> 22:41.170
Um, they're --
they're two lovely people

22:41.170 --> 22:42.790
who should be lovely
apart,

22:42.790 --> 22:46.170
and I'm just trying to figure
out how to help them get there.

22:46.170 --> 22:47.080
Oof.

22:47.080 --> 22:48.540
Well, in my experience,

22:48.540 --> 22:52.500
you just have to sit down
and talk and talk and talk

22:52.500 --> 22:56.920
until there's nothing left to do
but hug and say goodbye.

22:56.920 --> 22:58.960
My vote's
still for gambling.

22:58.960 --> 23:01.620
What about you, man?

23:01.620 --> 23:04.290
Well, I like to dump people
before midterms.

23:04.290 --> 23:05.580
Oh, come on.
That doesn't count.

23:05.580 --> 23:07.290
[ Chuckles ]

23:07.290 --> 23:09.620
Well, were you, uh, were you
seeing anyone in New York?

23:11.000 --> 23:14.250
Uh...

23:14.250 --> 23:16.830
Well, ye-- uh, yeah,
sort of. Um...

23:16.830 --> 23:18.460
How'd it end?

23:18.460 --> 23:19.830
Uh...

23:19.830 --> 23:22.790
Well, it's --
it's a really long story.

23:22.790 --> 23:24.420
Ooh, let me guess --

23:24.420 --> 23:27.580
in-- uh, instead of talking,
you ghosted

23:27.580 --> 23:29.500
and then came back home
and moved in with your sister?

23:29.500 --> 23:30.880
[ Chuckles ]

23:30.880 --> 23:32.750
Um...I guess
it wasn't that long.

23:32.750 --> 23:34.210
[ Chuckles ]

23:34.210 --> 23:35.210
Okay.

23:35.210 --> 23:40.290
I got a...
cake tasting to go to...

23:40.290 --> 23:42.210
for a wedding
that probably won't happen.

23:42.210 --> 23:44.920
Um, but I will
see you guys.

23:44.920 --> 23:46.170
See you later.

23:48.460 --> 23:50.000
Bye.

23:54.040 --> 23:55.960
Kevin!
[ Chuckles ]

23:55.960 --> 23:57.170
Dr. Sloane. Hi.

23:57.170 --> 23:58.750
I'm on the hunt
for pancakes.

23:58.750 --> 24:01.000
You want to join me?

24:01.000 --> 24:02.620
Uh...

24:02.620 --> 24:04.920
Listen, I'm sorry
that I've been avoiding you.

24:04.920 --> 24:06.210
No need to apologize.

24:06.210 --> 24:08.830
It was a mistake coming here --
but an honest one.

24:08.830 --> 24:11.290
I like you, Kevin.
I want to see you do well.

24:11.290 --> 24:13.580
And I am.
I'm doing really well,

24:13.580 --> 24:17.120
and I-I-I-I want to talk to you
about what's going on.

24:17.120 --> 24:19.710
Great. So do it.
Talk to me.

24:20.920 --> 24:23.420
[ Thunder rumbles ]

24:23.420 --> 24:24.710
Um...

24:24.710 --> 24:26.290
You know what -- I-I...

24:26.290 --> 24:29.880
I can't tell you,
but I think I can show you.

24:31.790 --> 24:33.170
Come on.

24:33.170 --> 24:40.210
♪♪

24:40.210 --> 24:41.620
Well, at least
he's talking to Dr. Sloane.

24:41.620 --> 24:43.750
Better than
talking to himself.

24:43.750 --> 24:45.330
He does that?

24:45.330 --> 24:47.080
Do you live
in our house?

24:49.620 --> 24:52.120
[ Bells jingle ]

24:52.120 --> 24:54.290
Hey!
Glad you came.

24:54.290 --> 24:56.040
Hey, can you explain
fondant?

24:56.040 --> 24:57.880
I mean,
it's pretty and all,

24:57.880 --> 24:59.880
but I think
we're a buttercream family.

24:59.880 --> 25:01.380
Who's this?

25:01.380 --> 25:04.170
Oh, this is Dr. Sloane,
my therapist.

25:07.330 --> 25:09.290
What do you think
about fondant?

25:11.830 --> 25:13.670
Can you read lips?

25:13.670 --> 25:14.750
It's weird
you're into this.

25:17.500 --> 25:18.670
What are you guys
doing?

25:18.670 --> 25:20.830
God! Nate!

25:20.830 --> 25:21.830
What's going on
in there?

25:21.830 --> 25:23.120
Spying on Kevin.

25:23.120 --> 25:25.040
We're not spying.
No.

25:25.040 --> 25:27.250
Mm-hmm. Well,
you're too exposed here.

25:27.250 --> 25:29.790
Better cover
at that window.

25:29.790 --> 25:31.960
Well,
now we're talking.

25:31.960 --> 25:34.580
Deb.
[ Chuckles ]

25:34.580 --> 25:37.580
Honesty is the foundation
of any relationship.

25:37.580 --> 25:40.790
Uh, I learned that little gem
from Dr. Sloane.

25:40.790 --> 25:42.210
Or TV. I don't remember.

25:42.210 --> 25:45.290
But the point is...

25:45.290 --> 25:48.460
I think you have to tell Ben
the truth.

25:50.040 --> 25:52.460
The -- The truth?

25:55.540 --> 25:57.670
The shrink saw me.
The shrink spotted me.

25:57.670 --> 25:59.250
Told you
not to get in their eyeline.

25:59.250 --> 26:01.580
We got to go. We got to go!
Let's go. Go, go, go.

26:01.580 --> 26:03.120
Amateurs.

26:05.080 --> 26:08.000
Uh, w-what's he
talking about, Pook?

26:08.000 --> 26:09.830
I...

26:12.620 --> 26:14.540
...want fondant.
[ Chuckles ]

26:14.540 --> 26:17.330
I'm sorry. I know
it doesn't taste as good.

26:17.330 --> 26:19.540
Deb, uh, if you don't tell him,
then I will.

26:19.540 --> 26:22.080
It's not a good idea
to force a confession, Kevin.

26:22.080 --> 26:24.210
-I know, but I think --
-What the hell's going on here?

26:28.330 --> 26:29.250
Ben.

26:31.500 --> 26:33.790
I love you so much.

26:35.920 --> 26:37.540
But...

26:37.540 --> 26:39.790
But what?

26:39.790 --> 26:45.120
♪♪

26:45.120 --> 26:47.540
I'm having an affair
with Kevin.

26:47.540 --> 26:48.330
What?

26:49.670 --> 26:50.830
Wait --

26:50.830 --> 26:53.040
[ Mariachi music plays ]

26:58.420 --> 27:00.880
[ Music continues ]

27:03.750 --> 27:07.580
[ Indistinct voices whispering ]

27:10.460 --> 27:12.040
Aah!

27:14.580 --> 27:17.250
Kevin, w-what the hell
are you doing?

27:18.540 --> 27:19.500
Helping?

27:23.580 --> 27:27.380
♪♪

27:27.380 --> 27:28.670
The coldest thing
they had.

27:28.670 --> 27:30.790
Oh, thank you.

27:30.790 --> 27:32.500
Kevin, maybe
I'm missing something,

27:32.500 --> 27:35.880
but how in the hell
is wrecking a marriage

27:35.880 --> 27:39.460
and getting punched in the face
supposed to be helping?

27:39.460 --> 27:40.920
I wish I could say.

27:40.920 --> 27:42.580
But you can't.
I get it. I get it.

27:42.580 --> 27:44.830
And -- And it's clear
you don't want my help,

27:44.830 --> 27:47.380
so I'm heading home.

27:47.380 --> 27:50.580
Call me
when you're ready to talk.

27:50.580 --> 27:52.920
Dr. Sloane, I'm sorry.

27:52.920 --> 27:55.120
You know --
You know what?

27:55.120 --> 27:59.580
Can I say something as --
as someone who cares about you?

27:59.580 --> 28:02.960
In the limited time
I've spent here,

28:02.960 --> 28:05.830
one thing
has become clear to me.

28:05.830 --> 28:07.710
Your sister is great.

28:10.170 --> 28:13.750
She drives me nuts,
but she's the best. Yeah.

28:13.750 --> 28:16.540
Remember that.

28:16.540 --> 28:18.750
Because she had plenty
on her plate

28:18.750 --> 28:21.500
before you dropped in
with your problems.

28:21.500 --> 28:23.710
You really think it's fair

28:23.710 --> 28:27.120
to make Amy
deal with all this chaos?

28:27.120 --> 28:29.830
I will --
I'll keep that in mind.

28:29.830 --> 28:32.250
You do that.

28:32.250 --> 28:34.580
And when you're ready --
hmm?

28:34.580 --> 28:40.460
♪♪

28:40.460 --> 28:42.460
[ Panting ]

28:42.460 --> 28:45.540
Focused today.
I like it.

28:45.540 --> 28:47.210
You training
for spy school?

28:49.120 --> 28:51.960
Slow down. Slow down.
I have shin splints.

28:53.670 --> 28:55.830
That spy thing --
that wasn't me.

28:55.830 --> 28:57.830
So, you went Mama Bear
on Kevin.

28:57.830 --> 28:59.540
I understand.

28:59.540 --> 29:01.420
He's lucky
to have a sister like you.

29:01.420 --> 29:03.120
Yeah, I keep hearing
what a great sister I am.

29:03.120 --> 29:04.460
It's not true.

29:07.250 --> 29:09.380
Look,
I don't think you know

29:09.380 --> 29:12.080
all of the reasons
that Kevin came back home.

29:12.080 --> 29:14.250
I just figured things
didn't work out in the city.

29:16.790 --> 29:19.080
Back in New York,

29:19.080 --> 29:21.710
Kevin was going through
some pretty heavy stuff.

29:21.710 --> 29:23.880
How heavy?

29:26.080 --> 29:27.880
He tried
to commit suicide.

29:31.330 --> 29:34.250
I'm...I'm so sorry.

29:35.920 --> 29:38.710
[ Voice breaking ]
Well, the thing is, um...

29:38.710 --> 29:40.920
he called me...

29:40.920 --> 29:43.380
before he did it.

29:43.380 --> 29:45.460
[ Exhales shakily ]

29:45.460 --> 29:47.580
He called me, and I saw
his number on the phone,

29:47.580 --> 29:49.290
and I, um...

29:49.290 --> 29:51.290
I didn't answer.

29:51.290 --> 29:52.920
Amy.

29:52.920 --> 29:56.420
I was mad at him.

29:56.420 --> 29:59.790
Kevin only ever called
if he needed something.

30:01.750 --> 30:04.500
And he did need something.

30:04.500 --> 30:06.420
Me.

30:09.500 --> 30:11.210
And I wasn't there
for him.

30:13.170 --> 30:14.830
I haven't been spying
on your brother,

30:14.830 --> 30:17.460
but from what I can see,
he's trying to move on.

30:17.460 --> 30:20.120
You should, too.

30:20.120 --> 30:25.830
♪♪

30:25.830 --> 30:26.750
Look, I don't want --

30:26.750 --> 30:28.170
I won't say a word.

30:29.670 --> 30:31.170
Okay, thanks.

30:34.380 --> 30:36.040
They were wearing
masks?

30:36.040 --> 30:38.000
Yeah,
big -- big red ones.

30:39.040 --> 30:41.170
And there was
a mariachi band?

30:41.170 --> 30:43.460
Now, that's a curveball.
Mm-hmm.

30:43.460 --> 30:45.290
But we're getting closer.

30:45.290 --> 30:48.210
Somehow, these visions are
a roadmap to find the righteous.

30:48.210 --> 30:51.210
Good job.
[ Scoffs ] Good job?

30:51.210 --> 30:52.540
I wrecked a marriage

30:52.540 --> 30:55.330
and destroyed
a lifelong friendship.

30:55.330 --> 30:57.170
Which is exactly
what you were supposed to do.

30:57.170 --> 30:59.170
Now,
I know it's difficult,

30:59.170 --> 31:02.170
but if the universe is happy,
we should move on.

31:03.920 --> 31:05.580
No.

31:05.580 --> 31:07.290
E-Excuse me?

31:07.290 --> 31:10.540
Ben and Deb deserve
a happy ending.

31:10.540 --> 31:12.670
The universe doesn't care
about happy endings.

31:12.670 --> 31:15.330
Well...I do.

31:15.330 --> 31:17.040
Wha--
[ Scoffs ]

31:24.330 --> 31:26.000
Oh! Hey. Sorry.

31:26.000 --> 31:27.710
Um...

31:27.710 --> 31:30.210
I'm heading out, so don't
wait for me to start dinner.

31:30.210 --> 31:31.920
I'm not sure what time
I'll -- I'll be back.

31:31.920 --> 31:33.750
-Okay. Yeah.
-Okay.

31:35.540 --> 31:37.830
Um...

31:37.830 --> 31:39.460
I talked
to Dr. Sloane today.

31:39.460 --> 31:40.830
Yeah?
How did it go?

31:40.830 --> 31:42.420
Uh, okay.

31:42.420 --> 31:45.380
I mean, not great.
It was...kind of terrible.

31:45.380 --> 31:46.670
He's leaving town.

31:46.670 --> 31:49.620
I'm sorry for springing him
on you like that.

31:49.620 --> 31:52.170
Well, hey...

31:52.170 --> 31:53.880
if you didn't
overstep your boundaries,

31:53.880 --> 31:55.040
then how would I know
you even care?

31:57.710 --> 32:01.710
His visit did -- did help me,
uh, realize a few things.

32:01.710 --> 32:04.830
Um...first of all...

32:04.830 --> 32:07.080
you are such a good s--

32:07.080 --> 32:09.750
Kevin, I swear to God, if you
say that I'm a good sister,

32:09.750 --> 32:12.880
I-I may start screaming,
and I may never stop.

32:14.080 --> 32:16.330
Okay, I ju-- I just
was gonna say you're a good...

32:16.330 --> 32:18.750
softball...player...

32:18.750 --> 32:20.420
'cause you play
a mean game of -- of softball.

32:23.170 --> 32:24.790
Um...

32:27.330 --> 32:30.120
Look, I know you think that
I'm not telling you something,

32:30.120 --> 32:32.420
and...

32:32.420 --> 32:33.920
you're right.

32:33.920 --> 32:35.420
You're right.

32:35.420 --> 32:38.460
But it's kind of --
it's kind of big.

32:38.460 --> 32:41.000
Um...

32:41.000 --> 32:43.420
[ Inhales sharply ]

32:43.420 --> 32:48.080
Just before everything,
uh, fell apart in New York,

32:48.080 --> 32:53.750
um, I bought an engagement ring
for my girlfriend,

32:53.750 --> 32:56.000
and she said no.

32:59.460 --> 33:01.380
And it was --
it was embarrassing,

33:01.380 --> 33:04.330
and I felt...
like an idiot.

33:04.330 --> 33:06.710
Like a blind idiot.
Kevin.

33:06.710 --> 33:10.250
But --
But helping these people

33:10.250 --> 33:14.170
is kind of helping me
process what happened.

33:16.250 --> 33:19.120
And I know
that sounds crazy, but...

33:19.120 --> 33:20.420
it's the truth.

33:23.330 --> 33:24.830
Wow.

33:24.830 --> 33:27.460
Well...
thank you for telling me.

33:27.460 --> 33:28.710
[ Both chuckle ]

33:30.500 --> 33:32.330
And good luck with that.

33:32.330 --> 33:34.540
Thanks.

33:34.540 --> 33:38.420
Oh, and, Aim,
for what it's worth,

33:38.420 --> 33:41.790
you really are
a great softball player.

33:41.790 --> 33:43.580
[ Chuckles ]
Get out of here.

33:43.580 --> 33:44.750
[ Door opens ]

33:47.460 --> 33:50.750
Kevin, that's terrible.
I'm so sorry.

33:50.750 --> 33:52.710
Uh, it wasn't true.

33:52.710 --> 33:54.080
Excuse me?

33:54.080 --> 33:57.330
That whole story
was a-a lie.

33:57.330 --> 33:59.040
I just needed
the right motivation.

34:03.120 --> 34:06.250
Well, it was almost like
something that happened.

34:06.250 --> 34:08.920
[ Truck door opens ]

34:08.920 --> 34:10.830
[ Crickets chirping ]

34:17.250 --> 34:20.710
So, this is
where you got engaged?

34:20.710 --> 34:22.880
How'd you know that?

34:22.880 --> 34:25.420
Uh, Ben told me.

34:25.420 --> 34:28.250
He said you liked to
come up here to clear your head,

34:28.250 --> 34:30.920
and he surprised you.

34:30.920 --> 34:32.000
Surprise!

34:32.000 --> 34:33.420
What do you want,
Kevin?

34:33.420 --> 34:35.880
Uh...

34:35.880 --> 34:39.040
why did you lie to Ben?

34:41.880 --> 34:43.830
'm sorry you got punched.

34:43.830 --> 34:45.710
But you put me
on the spot.

34:45.710 --> 34:47.670
That's my fault.

34:47.670 --> 34:49.790
If I had just told him
that I didn't love him,

34:49.790 --> 34:51.040
he would never
accept that.

34:52.790 --> 34:56.380
He'd spend the rest of his life
trying to win me back.

34:56.380 --> 34:57.830
But now he hates my guts,

34:57.830 --> 35:01.290
so he can move on with his life
and forget about me.

35:02.830 --> 35:04.670
Is that what you want?

35:07.170 --> 35:10.210
Is that
what you want, Deb?

35:10.210 --> 35:12.460
For me
to forget about you?

35:12.460 --> 35:13.710
[ Sighs ]

35:13.710 --> 35:15.790
No.

35:15.790 --> 35:17.580
You're my best friend.

35:20.540 --> 35:22.420
But I'm not
in love with you.

35:24.380 --> 35:25.540
Well,
if I'm your best friend,

35:25.540 --> 35:28.000
why couldn't you
just tell me the truth?

35:28.000 --> 35:32.170
Because...I know you.

35:32.170 --> 35:34.170
Tell me I'm wrong.

35:38.170 --> 35:40.460
I just...

35:40.460 --> 35:43.540
I can't believe...

35:43.540 --> 35:45.170
I thought you'd cheat on me
with this guy.

35:46.540 --> 35:48.330
Yeah.
It's...funny.

35:48.330 --> 35:50.500
He's not even close
to my type.

35:50.500 --> 35:51.880
Well,
I don't know about --

35:51.880 --> 35:53.000
It's not like
you're out of shape,

35:53.000 --> 35:54.040
but you're not exactly
in shape, either.

35:54.040 --> 35:55.540
All right. Fine.

35:55.540 --> 35:57.750
You kind of got
that quirky/cute thing going on.

35:57.750 --> 35:59.250
Thanks, Ben.
I'd definitely say
more quirky than cute.

35:59.250 --> 36:01.210
Got it!

36:01.210 --> 36:02.540
[ Sighs ]

36:02.540 --> 36:05.040
I-I don't expect you
to forgive me,

36:05.040 --> 36:07.790
but I was
thinking of you.

36:07.790 --> 36:10.330
We'll figure it out.

36:10.330 --> 36:12.120
It's gonna take
some time.

36:15.120 --> 36:16.920
[ Sniffles ]

36:16.920 --> 36:18.290
Can we have
a little privacy?

36:18.290 --> 36:21.250
Huh? Oh. [ Sniffles ]
Yeah.

36:21.250 --> 36:22.290
[ Thud ]
Aaaaaaah!

36:27.540 --> 36:28.880
I'm okay!

36:30.830 --> 36:33.580
We'll get some help!

36:33.580 --> 36:36.540
I like you better
when you're asleep.

36:36.540 --> 36:41.580
♪♪

36:41.580 --> 36:47.080
♪♪

36:47.080 --> 36:50.670
This is a really sweet setup
you've got here.

36:50.670 --> 36:52.540
It's not mine.

36:52.540 --> 36:56.250
I could see myself
sitting out here in a blanket

36:56.250 --> 36:58.670
with some tea
and a nice book.

36:58.670 --> 37:01.120
If I brew or drank tea.

37:01.120 --> 37:02.670
Or read books.

37:02.670 --> 37:04.790
Or used blankets.

37:04.790 --> 37:07.120
Where is everyone? Did you
tell them the right time?

37:07.120 --> 37:08.120
I did.

37:11.040 --> 37:12.880
They're not coming.

37:12.880 --> 37:15.420
What do you mean?

37:15.420 --> 37:17.540
What -- There isn't
gonna be a meeting?

37:17.540 --> 37:20.290
They're not really
feeling the mission anymore.

37:20.290 --> 37:23.540
So...the two of us
are just supposed to

37:23.540 --> 37:27.670
find out what happened
to the other 35 by ourselves?

37:27.670 --> 37:29.580
[ Sighing ] Yeah.

37:29.580 --> 37:33.210
Thing is,
I think I might be done, too.

37:33.210 --> 37:35.120
Ava!

37:35.120 --> 37:36.790
Why?!

37:36.790 --> 37:38.960
We -- We still have
a job to do.

37:38.960 --> 37:41.710
Not anymore.
We failed!

37:41.710 --> 37:42.790
That's not true.

37:42.790 --> 37:44.540
We still have hope.
We still have Kevin.

37:44.540 --> 37:47.080
You have Kevin.

37:47.080 --> 37:49.620
The rest of us
have no one.

37:49.620 --> 37:51.830
That's not true.

37:51.830 --> 37:53.670
We still have each other.

37:53.670 --> 38:02.500
♪♪

38:02.500 --> 38:04.420
[ Sighs ]

38:04.420 --> 38:07.710
[ Owl hoots ]

38:07.710 --> 38:12.000
♪♪

38:12.000 --> 38:14.790
[ Crickets chirping ]

38:14.790 --> 38:16.290
Hey.
Where have you been?

38:16.290 --> 38:17.710
I've been looking all over
for you.

38:17.710 --> 38:19.290
Right here.

38:19.290 --> 38:20.710
Well, dinner's ready.

38:20.710 --> 38:21.880
Have you seen Kevin?

38:21.880 --> 38:23.120
Uh, nope.

38:23.120 --> 38:24.790
Okay. Come on.

38:28.210 --> 38:35.330
♪♪

38:35.330 --> 38:42.170
♪♪

38:42.170 --> 38:44.540
I'm really proud of you.

38:44.540 --> 38:48.710
You went above and beyond
for two people you barely know.

38:48.710 --> 38:50.040
That, my friend,
is growth.

38:53.000 --> 38:55.540
I'm trying to be nice to you,
and you're ruining it.

38:55.540 --> 38:57.830
Why aren't you happy?

38:58.880 --> 39:00.790
Amy.

39:00.790 --> 39:02.790
I'll just -- I'll have to
keep lying to her,

39:02.790 --> 39:06.790
and, I mean, I get why that is,
and I'll do it,

39:06.790 --> 39:10.290
but it's never
gonna feel right.

39:10.290 --> 39:13.290
And there isn't really anything
you can say to change that.

39:15.460 --> 39:16.960
Good.

39:19.500 --> 39:21.790
Because that's
a sign of growth, too.

39:21.790 --> 39:24.960
Your pie, sir.

39:24.960 --> 39:27.040
Sweet shiner,
by the way.

39:27.040 --> 39:29.880
Oof! That have anything
to do with the marriage
you were gonna torpedo?

39:29.880 --> 39:31.500
Uh...it's a souvenir.

39:31.500 --> 39:33.580
-Oh.
-[ Chuckles ] You got off lucky.

39:33.580 --> 39:35.000
You ever been punched
in the butt?

39:36.540 --> 39:39.250
-Like, hard.
-No.

39:39.250 --> 39:42.500
Uh, I'm glad
that you're -- you're here.

39:42.500 --> 39:47.000
I, uh, wanted to talk to you
about this morning.

39:47.000 --> 39:49.920
I'm -- I'm so sorry
for that joke I made

39:49.920 --> 39:51.170
about your girlfriend
in New York,

39:51.170 --> 39:53.330
-and I just feel so --
-Oh! No.

39:53.330 --> 39:56.210
I-I completely see
how that could be, uh...

39:56.210 --> 39:58.170
seen as a likely scenario.
[ Chuckles ]

40:00.460 --> 40:02.290
Um...

40:02.290 --> 40:05.380
But -- But...
the truth is,

40:05.380 --> 40:08.710
I didn't come home
because of a -- of a breakup.

40:08.710 --> 40:11.670
I, uh...

40:11.670 --> 40:16.290
Back in New York, I was in a --
a really dark place,

40:16.290 --> 40:21.080
and, uh...so I...

40:21.080 --> 40:24.750
I got incredibly drunk...

40:24.750 --> 40:29.250
and that didn't make me
feel better.

40:29.250 --> 40:31.960
[ Chuckles ]

40:31.960 --> 40:36.250
And I-I decided
that I just...

40:36.250 --> 40:38.380
wanted it to end.

40:40.750 --> 40:42.460
But the...

40:42.460 --> 40:46.460
the thing I found out
about feeling that way

40:46.460 --> 40:49.170
is that, um...

40:49.170 --> 40:50.710
it always passes.

40:50.710 --> 40:52.460
Or it -- it -- it --
it -- it did for me.

40:52.460 --> 40:55.040
And...

40:55.040 --> 40:58.040
like, I feel...good.

40:58.040 --> 40:59.880
[ Chuckles ]

40:59.880 --> 41:01.920
And now I'm back home,

41:01.920 --> 41:05.290
with my family and --
and -- and with you guys,

41:05.290 --> 41:07.210
[ Chuckling ]
and that's awesome.

41:09.420 --> 41:11.250
Thank you
for telling us that.

41:11.250 --> 41:13.500
It's...

41:13.500 --> 41:16.380
I -- I can't even imagine how
hard that must've been for you.

41:16.380 --> 41:18.710
Um...

41:18.710 --> 41:21.210
actually, it was harder
trying to lie about it.

41:23.830 --> 41:26.540
I have a vestigial tail.

41:26.540 --> 41:27.710
Hm?

41:29.580 --> 41:31.210
What?

41:31.210 --> 41:33.000
I thought we were, like,
going around the table,

41:33.000 --> 41:35.290
making confessions, and...

41:35.290 --> 41:36.290
Uh...

41:36.290 --> 41:38.250
I-I, uh, um...

41:38.250 --> 41:42.670
I sometimes sneak outside food
into movie theaters.

41:42.670 --> 41:44.670
Yeah, I...

41:44.670 --> 41:46.710
I sometimes talk about myself
in the third person.

41:46.710 --> 41:48.210
Okay, well, that's not bad.
That's --

41:48.210 --> 41:50.750
No, no, no, no, but when I do,
I call myself "Lil Kevvy."

41:50.750 --> 41:53.580
[ Laughter ]

41:53.580 --> 41:56.120
Oh, I still suck my thumb
sometimes.
Oh...

41:59.960 --> 42:08.210
♪♪

42:08.210 --> 42:16.380
♪♪

42:16.380 --> 42:24.580
♪♪

42:24.580 --> 42:32.500
♪♪
